QUICK REFERENCE
-----------------------------------------------------------

wget URL                         Download the binary
chmod +x filename                Give the binary execute permission
gdb filename                     Open in GDB
info functions                   List all functions
disas main                       Disassemble main function
break *0xADDRESS                 Set breakpoint at an address
run                              Run the program until breakpoint hits
x/4xb $rbp-0x4                  Examine 4 bytes at memory address


-----------------------------------------------------------
THE FLAG
-----------------------------------------------------------

picoCTF{0x6bc96222}


-----------------------------------------------------------
KEY TAKEAWAYS
-----------------------------------------------------------

Endianness matters. x86 is little-endian which means bytes are stored in
memory in reverse order compared to how we write them. This is one of the
most important concepts in reverse engineering and binary exploitation.

The x/4xb command is essential for reading raw memory. It lets you see
exactly what is sitting at any address byte by byte.

Breakpoints are how you pause a program at the right moment. Setting one
right after a memory store lets you inspect the value before anything else
changes it.

Always read the challenge description carefully. This one told you exactly
which command to use and exactly how to format the flag.
